# Pre-Deploy Validation Checklist

Run these checks locally before any deployment. **Stop the deploy if any check fails.**

## 1. Vite build (catches broken imports, JSX errors)
```powershell
npm run build
```
Must exit 0. This is the most important gate — if the build fails, the deploy will fail on Databricks too.

## 2. Python syntax check (catches syntax errors in backend)
```powershell
python -m py_compile main.py
python -m py_compile db.py
Get-ChildItem routers\*.py | ForEach-Object { python -m py_compile $_.FullName }
```
Must produce no errors.

## 3. Linter checks
- Run `ReadLints` on every file modified in this session
- All errors introduced by this session must be resolved
- Pre-existing warnings are acceptable (there are ~210 pre-existing ESLint issues)

## 4. Critical file integrity
Verify these files exist and are non-empty:
- `app.yaml` — must contain the uvicorn command
- `main.py` — FastAPI entry point
- `db.py` — database connection module
- `index.html` — frontend shell
- `requirements.txt` — Python deps
- `package.json` — Node deps with `build` script

## 5. API contract check
If any router (`routers/*.py`) endpoint signature changed:
- Verify the matching frontend call in `src/data/databricksData.js` is updated
- Check field names match between backend response and frontend expectations

## 6. Post-deploy verification (after deploy succeeds)
```powershell
databricks apps get hertz-leo-leadsmgmtsystem --output json
```
- Confirm `app_status.state` is `RUNNING`
- Confirm `active_deployment.status.state` is `SUCCEEDED`
- Hit the app URL to verify: `https://hertz-leo-leadsmgmtsystem-1957546315544672.aws.databricksapps.com/`

## 7. On deploy failure — check app logs
If Step 6 shows a failed or unhealthy state, pull app logs immediately:
```powershell
databricks apps logs hertz-leo-leadsmgmtsystem --profile DanSiaoAuth --tail-lines 200
```
- `[SYSTEM]` lines = build/install errors (npm, pip, vite)
- `[APP]` lines = Python runtime errors (tracebacks, import failures)
- Filter for errors only:
  ```powershell
  databricks apps logs hertz-leo-leadsmgmtsystem --profile DanSiaoAuth --tail-lines 500 --search "ERROR"
  ```
Report the error to the user with the exact log lines before attempting any fix.
